article.headline: Creighton 73, Bradley 64
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Cavel Witter came off the bench to score 14 points and lead Creighton to a 73-64 victory over Bradley on Saturday night. Creighton (13-4, 3-2 Missouri Valley) led by one point going into half time and came back from the break to widen its lead by eight points in the second period and seal the win. Bradley (10-6, 4-1 Missouri Valley) saw its shooting fall from 40.9 percent in the first period to 34.4 percent in the second. Antoine Young added 13 points for the Bluejays. Creighton earned 33 points from its bench players. Dodie Dunson led Bradley with 16 points. Theron Wilson and Sam Maniscalco had 15 points each for the Braves. Chris Roberts had a game-high nine rebounds for Bradley.
